Magic Resume Commercial Restrictions & User Agreement (English)

Welcome to Magic Resume. This software is open-sourced under the Apache License 2.0, with strict commercial use restrictions attached. By continuing to use this software, you agree to the terms outlined below.

I. Free for Personal Use
This software is free to use only for personal, non-commercial purposes (such as personal learning, skill exchange, and creating personal resumes).

II. Commercial License Required
Unauthorized commercial use is strictly prohibited. Any organization or individual must contact the author in advance to obtain a commercial license if any of the following conditions are met, regardless of whether the source code has been modified:
1. Providing this software as a service (such as SaaS, PaaS, or online tool websites) directly or indirectly to the public for commercial gain (including but not limited to charging fees, placing commercial advertisements, or driving traffic to other platforms).
2. Embedding or integrating this software or its derivative versions into other commercial software, closed-source products, or internal enterprise business systems.
3. Conducting secondary development on this software (including but not limited to modifying the application name, logo, code, and functionality) for commercial operations.

III. Contributor Agreement
As a contributor to Magic Resume, you agree to the following:
1. License Adjustment: The maintainers reserve the right to adjust the open-source license and additional terms as needed.
2. Commercial Use: Any code you contribute may be used for commercial purposes, including but not limited to commercial license distribution and cloud business operations.

IV. Other Terms
1. The interpretation of these terms is subject to the discretion of Magic Resume developers.
2. These terms may be updated, and users will be notified through the software when changes occur.
For any questions or to request a commercial license, please contact the Magic Resume development team.

Apart from the specific commercial restrictions mentioned above, all other rights and restrictions follow the Apache License 2.0.


